  "text": "The various tissues obtained from experimental animals fixed in 10 % formosaline were dehydrated in graded alcohol, embedded in paraffin, and cut into 4-5 μm thick sections. Hematoxylin-eosin was used to stain the sections for photomicroscopic assessment using a Model N-400ME photomicroscope (CEL-TECH Di-agnostics, Hamburg, Germany). Slides were examined using the × 40, × 100, and × 400 objectives (Galigher and Kozloff, 1971; [CITATION_1] .",
